  "sections": {
    "Description": "The Scorpion resembles the creature it is named after, stinger included. It is able to be encountered from the start as a regular enemy. Its goal is to restrict units' mobility with webbing, then attack them.",
    "Strategy": "The Scorpion is dangerous during the early game for two reasons:\n  - If it webs one of your mechs, you may be forced to make inefficient moves with your other mechs to free the webbed mech.\n  - It has 3 health, and relatively few starting mechs are capable of dealing 3 damage in one turn.\nIts weakness is its low mobility, so deploying your mechs where they can still escape webbing while dealing with other threats is imperative.  Alternatively, if you keep your mechs just out of its movement range, it will waste its web attack on grid buildings, which are already stationary.  Your mechs will then be free to push it or kill it on the following turn."
  },
  "full_text": "Scorpion\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n3\nSystems\nStinging Spinneret\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nWeb an adjacent target, preparing to stab it for 1 damage.\nScorpion\nis one of the\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Scorpion resembles the creature it is named after, stinger included. It is able to be encountered from the start as a regular enemy. Its goal is to restrict units' mobility with webbing, then attack them.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nThe Scorpion is dangerous during the early game for two reasons:\nIf it webs one of your mechs, you may be forced to make inefficient moves with your other mechs to free the webbed mech.\nIt has 3 health, and relatively few starting mechs are capable of dealing 3 damage in one turn.\nIts weakness is its low mobility, so deploying your mechs where they can still escape webbing while dealing with other threats is imperative.  Alternatively, if you keep your mechs just out of its movement range, it will waste its web attack on grid buildings, which are already stationary.  Your mechs will then be free to push it or kill it on the following turn.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
